values: 赚；赚得；挣得；获得；赢得；得到（尊重、名声等）；招致；引起；生息；获利

synonym.mean: 赚，赚得；获得，挣得；使得到；博得

word_mean_info__list.difference: 强调通过不断的、持续的努力而获得某物，也指日积月累地渐渐地获得。书面语用词。
较正式用词，着重通过巨大努力、要求而得到所需或盼望已久的东西。
普通用词，使用广泛，可指以任何方式得到某物，也不一定要经过努力。
强调要通过努力或竞争，或需要付出代价才能获得所渴望的东西。
主要指通过努力、斗争、比赛等而获得胜利。
侧重指依靠自己的劳动或因付出代价与有功而获得。
侧重指经过努力或有意识行动而取得某种成就或获得某种利益或好处。

word_group.brief_definition: 挣钱谋生, 挣钱生活
收入可观；收入与预付金（或版税）相当
因勇敢而被封为骑士；初次脱颖而出；初次获得荣誉
谋生；挣饭吃；值得为之花费时间

bilingual.source: He works hard to earn a reward.
bilingual.target: 他努力工作以获得报酬。

bilingual.source: He works hard to earn higher income.
bilingual.target: 他努力工作以获得高工资。

bilingual.source: You need to earn 30 credits to graduate.
bilingual.target: 你需要获得30个学分才能毕业。

bilingual.source: He is taking online courses to earn his degree.
bilingual.target: 他正在上网课以获得学位。

bilingual.source: You can earn credits through online courses.
bilingual.target: 你可以通过在线课程获得学分。

bilingual.source: She is working hard to earn her college degree.
bilingual.target: 她正在努力获得她的大专学历。

bilingual.source: This coupon allows you to earn double points.
bilingual.target: 这个优惠券可以让你获得加倍的积分。

bilingual.source: Postgraduate education can help you earn a higher degree.
bilingual.target: 研究生教育可以帮助你获得更高的学位。

bilingual.source: Foreign trade can help a country earn more foreign exchange.
bilingual.target: 对外贸易可以帮助国家获得更多的外汇收入。

bilingual.source: The team needs to earn more points to win the championship.
bilingual.target: 这个队需要获得更多的分数才能赢得冠军。

list.abstract: earn（英 [ɜːn]，美 [ɜːrn]），英语单词，动词，为赚得；挣得；获得。短语搭配有earn a living（挣钱谋生，挣钱生活）。例句为“He was eager to earn money.（他渴望挣钱。）” earn相关近义词有acquire、buy等。第三人称单数earns，现在分词earning，过去式earned，过去分词earned。

yingyinNormal.en: I was sent undercover to earn Lane's trust, and eventually identify the members of his organization.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我被秘密派遣来获得莱恩的信任，并且最终指认这个组织的成员们。

yingyinNormal.en: No, of course. We need to earn their trust.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然，我们需要赢得他们的信任。

yingyinNormal.en: To earn money I worked as a mother's helper.
See, Caroline was about to earn her company billions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 卡罗琳本来马上就要为她的公司赢利亿万。

yingyinNormal.en: She even cares about me. And I've done very little to earn that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她甚至很关心我，虽然我几乎啥也没做。

yingyinNormal.en: A day? There are children in a sneaker factory in Indonia who out earn you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一天？连印度尼西亚的球鞋场童工都赚得比你多。

yingyinNormal.en: Your triumphs will earn you points. Any rule-breaking and you will lose points.
yingyinNormal.zh: 表现好能为学院加分，哪个学院有人违反校规就得扣分。

yingyinNormal.en: Listen, we could always earn more money, okay? But, we're only gonna get married once.
yingyinNormal.zh: 钱可以再赚，我们只结婚一次。

yingyinNormal.en: So let's make sure women earn equal pay for equal work, and have a fair shot at success.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因此，让我们确保妇女能够同工同酬，并在成功上有相同的机会。

yingyinNormal.en: It's foolish, I suppose, for a creature like me, to hope that one day he might earn your affection.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我这样一定很傻，一头野兽竟期待着有一天能得到你的青睐。

yingyinNormal.en: So, I'm hitting the road to earn your vote, because it's your time, and I hope you'll join me on this journey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因此我需要你的选票，因为这是你的时代，我希望你能和我一起踏上征程。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you talking about? Keep it. It's not mine. I didn't earn it. If I kept it, it would be like stealing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别傻了，留着自己用吧，这些钱不是我的，我留下来就如同偷窃。

yingyinNormal.en: If you want to speak to the girl again, earn yourself some phone time! This is inhuman, this is insane! Mycroft, we know!
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你们想再跟小姑娘说话，就给自己争取点时间。这太没人性，太疯狂了！麦考夫，我们知道！

yingyinNormal.en: My father set him up with his own firm. He gave us the house that we live in, the Hamptons, the boat. He's never had to earn a dime.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我父亲让他在自己公司工作，他给了我们房子，汉普顿的别墅，游艇，他一分钱都不用挣。

yingyinNormal.en: The Fed not only determines how much that paper in your wallet is worth，but also your chances of getting or keeping the job where you earn it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 联准会不只决定你荷包里那些纸张的价值，还掌握了你得到或保住工作的机会，也就是你赚钱的饭碗。

yingyinNormal.en: The Fed not only determines how much that paper in your wallet is worth，but also your chances of getting or keeping the job where you earn it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 联准会不只决定你荷包里那些纸张的价值，还掌握了你得到或保住工作的机会，也就是你赚钱的饭碗。

yingyinNormal.en: Say, for example, the Eurozone tries to lower its interest rate and reduce unemployment. Money flows out to earn higher interest rates elsewhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 举例来说，欧元使用区试着想要降低利率来减少失业。这样资金就会流到别的国家来争取更高的利率。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, well, this is what you're gonna do. You're gonna get a job. You're gonna get an apartment. And then you will live off the money that you earn.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你现在要做的是找一份工作，找一间公寓，然后靠你自己赚的钱过活。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: deserve as a result of labor or service

examination_example.sentence: Everything he achieved in life was <highlight>earned</highlight> the hard way and his success in the literary field was no exception.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他一生中所取得的一切都是通过艰苦的努力应得的，他在文学领域的成功也不例外。

examination_example.sentence: Through a more diffuse "halo effect," whereby its good deeds <highlight>earn</highlight> it greater consideration from consumers and others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通过“光环效应”的进一步扩散，该公司的善行使得消费者和他人更多的考虑该公司。

examination_example.sentence: In the past, workers with average skills, doing an average job, could <highlight>earn</highlight> an average lifestyle.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在过去，技能一般、工作一般的工人可以获得一般的生活方式。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person) obtain money in return for labor or services

examination_example.sentence: Our other education related exports <highlight>earn</highlight> up to £10 billion a year more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们其他与教育相关的出口一年则可以赚多达100亿英镑。

examination_example.sentence: The English language teaching sector directly <highlight>earns</highlight> nearly £1.3 billion for the UK.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英语培训行业为英国直接赚取了将近13亿英镑。

examination_example.sentence: Being average just won't <highlight>earn</highlight> you what it used to.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 平庸不会给你带来以前的收入。

word_usage.usage: earn既可作及物动词，又可作不及物动词。作及物动词时，其后可接名词或代词，如：earn a fortune
表示“使某人赢得某物”可以用earn sb. sth.表达，也可用介词for来表达：earn sth. for sb.

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person) obtain money in return for labor or services
deserve as a result of labor or service

examination_example.sentence: Instead of instantly satisfying their wishes, parents should help them work out a plan to <highlight>earn</highlight> things they'd like to have.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 父母不应该立即满足他们的愿望，而是应该帮助他们制定一个计划来获得他们想要的东西。

examination_example.sentence: It <highlight>earned</highlight> Coca-Cola an iconic image that made it part of American culture for a century.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它为可口可乐赢得了一个标志性的形象，使其成为美国文化的一部分长达一个世纪。

examination_example.sentence: It was 100 years ago this week that the bottle <highlight>earned</highlight> a patent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 100年前的这个星期，瓶子获得了专利。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 强调通过不断的、持续的努力而获得某物, 也指日积月累地渐渐地获得。书面语用词。如：acquire knowledge(获得知识)。
为正式用词, 多用于庄重场合, 主要指通过努力达到重要目的或得到珍贵的东西。如：The scientist attained great fame by a new discovery.(那科学家由于一次新发现而出了名。)
侧重指依靠自己的劳动或因付出代价与有功而获得。
侧重指经过努力或有意识行动而取得某种成就或获得某种利益或好处。
普通用词, 使用广泛, 可指以任何方式得到某物, 也不一定要经过努力。
较正式用词, 着重通过巨大努力、要求而得到所需或盼望已久的东西。

examination_example.sentence: When farmers give up trying to <highlight>earn</highlight> a living from farming or herding, trees simply move in.

examination_example.sentence: Students of color are more engaged and <highlight>earn</highlight> better grades when they see themselves in their studies.

examination_example.sentence: Graduation requirements specify the number of credits you must <highlight>earn</highlight> and the minimum grade point average you must achieve.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毕业要求规定了你必须获得的学分数和你必须达到的最低平均绩点。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person) obtain money in return for labor or services

examination_example.sentence: Would you like the opportunity to <highlight>earn</highlight> extra cash close to home?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你希望有机会在家附近赚取额外的现金吗？

examination_example.sentence: He was eager to <highlight>earn</highlight> money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他渴望挣钱。

examination_example.sentence: He discovered that he could <highlight>earn</highlight> some money while doing something he really enjoyed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他发现他可以一边赚钱，一边做他真正喜欢的事情。

examination_example.sentence: The admiration and respect his uncle <highlight>earned</highlight> inspired Nielsen to make a career (职业) in acting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他叔叔所赢得的钦佩和尊重激励尼尔森投身表演事业。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2018-2021年全国重点省市中考试卷，包括听力、阅读、完形、单选、填空、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: (of a person) obtain money in return for labor or services

examination_example.sentence: But his father could not <highlight>earn</highlight> enough money to give his family a good life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但他的父亲无法赚到足够的钱来让家人过上好日子。

examination_example.sentence: They planted grapes to <highlight>earn</highlight> money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们种植葡萄是为了挣钱。

examination_example.sentence: This summer there are things that students can do to <highlight>earn</highlight> some pocket money or to help others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这个夏天，学生们可以做一些事情来赚取一些零花钱或帮助他人。

sense_info_list.en: to get sth that you deserve, usually because of sth good you have done or because of the good qualities you have

examination_example.sentence: I liked to show off (炫耀) in front of others to <highlight>earn</highlight> their praise.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我喜欢在别人面前炫耀以赢得他们的赞扬。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Earn</highlight> yourself an official Junior Ranger Badge!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为自己赢得一个正式的少年骑警徽章!

examination_example.sentence: In Manson’s opinion, students should be encouraged to <highlight>earn</highlight> school uniforms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在曼森看来，应该鼓励学生赢得校服。
